The paper discusses the use of bibliometric indicators for research assessment, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. However, the focus on citation-based metrics and research evaluation suggests that the paper is most likely to belong to the Digital Libraries (cs.DL) sub-category. Other relevant sub-categories include Cybersecurity (cs.CY), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
